&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Session Description: &lt;/b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight:400;&quot;&gt;Participants will engage in a practical workshop in which they learn how to adapt and create end-of-unit cultural reflections using Boise State’s OER text Français inclusif. Presenters will share sample reflections and explain how to choose diverse topics and artifacts with cultural significance for a thematic unit. Participants will gain insight on the impact of cultural reflections on student engagement and retention in language programs. Canva templates and guided work time will be provided so that teachers can leave with a product to use this year. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;b&gt;Session Outcomes:&lt;/b&gt; &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight:400;&quot;&gt;Participants will learn how to adapt Cultural Reflection templates from Boise State University's Français inclusif OER Pressbooks for their own classrooms, language and thematic units. They will understand the impact cultural reflections will have on students’ cultural competency and potential program retention. &lt;/span&gt;
